Why CSP is powerful

Most real problems aren’t single-answer questions.

They’re:
	•	multi-actor
	•	multi-incentive
	•	multi-constraint

Examples:

Domain	CSP example
economics	policies that balance growth, fairness, stability
engineering	design that meets cost, strength, weight
AI	scheduling, routing, planning
biology	protein folding
diplomacy	agreements acceptable to all parties

In all of them the goal is:

Find a configuration where nothing breaks.

